name: Lt. Governor Matt Pinnell
tweet: In DC this week for mtgs with Lt. Governors from across the country. Was able to participate in a policy panel on workforce development and combating inflation. Excited to share what we’re doing in Oklahoma and learn from other Lt. Governors.  https://t.co/ahZtmqGEc2

name: Lt. Governor Matt Pinnell
tweet: Great discussion with the House Veterans Caucus last week. Oklahoma was recently ranked in the top 5 states for veterans. With 12 VA clinics, high income levels, and resources for veteran-owned businesses, our state honors former servicemen and women by making them a priority.  https://t.co/4S4gotSs6R

name: Lt. Governor Matt Pinnell
tweet: I’m proud to support the Rural Broadband Expansion Act, which proposes a plan to get 95% of Oklahomans broadband coverage in the next 5 years. Internet access is not just a quality of life issue; it’s an economic development issue as well. Read more below.  https://t.co/grDx8kVAiE

name: Lt. Governor Matt Pinnell
